    "body": "Hello all,\n\nI was running `:checkhealth` on release and nightly builds.  I am running all of this on Windows 11.  \n\nThe release version reports correctly that Ruby is installed, but the nightly version does not.\n\n# Release (correct)\n\n```\nNVIM v0.11.6\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1741730670\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n```\n \n```\nRuby provider (optional) ~\n- Ruby: ruby 3.4.8 (2025-12-17 revision 995b59f666) +PRISM [x64-mingw-ucrt]\n- Host: C:\\Ruby34-x64\\bin\\neovim-ruby-host.bat\n- ✅ OK Latest \"neovim\" gem is installed: 0.10.0\n```\n\n# Nightly (incorrect)\n\n```\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2474+g3b621d4180\nBuild type: RelWithDebInfo\nLuaJIT 2.1.1772148810\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n```\n\n```\nRuby provider (optional) ~\n- Ruby: 3.4.8\n- Host: C:\\Ruby34-x64\\bin\\neovim-ruby-host.bat\n- ❌ ERROR Failed to run: cmd /c gem list -ra \"\"\"^^neovim$\"\"\"\n  - ADVICE:\n    - Make sure you're connected to the internet.\n    - Are you behind a firewall or proxy? \n```\n",
